England Sets Sri Lanka Target of 230 in Shortened One-Day Game

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-06-28T18:19:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/england-sets-sri-lanka-target-of-230-in-shortened-one-day-game.html
England  set  Sri Lanka  a total of 230
in their rain-shortened opening one-day cricket match at the
Oval in  London .  Craig Kieswetter  scored 61 and Eoin Morgan had 45 to help
England reach 229-8. The match was reduced to 32 overs each
after a lengthy weather delay.  The five-game series continues at Headingley in Leeds on
July 1.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  